      <item>
        <title>My first Rmd blog post!</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Following &lt;a href=&quot;http://brendanrocks.com/blogging-with-rmarkdown-knitr-jekyll/&quot;&gt;this blog&lt;/a&gt; it is straightforward to set up the jekyll site. The only problem I encountered is that &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;XCode&lt;/code&gt; automatically jumps up to try to open the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;.md&lt;/code&gt; file. This was resolved by going into &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;system preferences &amp;gt; default apps&lt;/code&gt;, and set the default app for &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;.md, .r, .Rmd&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;RStudio&lt;/code&gt; rather than &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;XCode&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Next questions:&lt;/p&gt;

