        <title>My second Rmd post</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Well, I thought I disabled XCode from automatically popping up. It still does.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Secondly, this workflow automatically adds &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;/knitr-jekyll&lt;/code&gt; before the URL for figures, resulting something like &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;/knitr-jekyllfigure/...&lt;/code&gt;. This was done at the knitr from Rmd to md. It’s in the md.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then I did some test, and changed the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;baseurl: &quot;&quot;&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;baseurl: &quot;/&quot;&lt;/code&gt; in &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;_config.yml&lt;/code&gt;, the URL is fixed. But doing so would ruin the rest of the pages – the “about” page becomes &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;http://about/&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now I am going back, and just have to manually do this.&lt;/p&gt;

